args: With Halloween season in full swing once again,\nthe Halidom's denizens decided to mark the\noccasion by holding a celebration with the locals.
Trick or treat! I hope you brought candy,\nbecause otherwise I'll have to eeeeat\nyour braaaaaains...
Oh, what an adorable little zombie!\nHere's a gumdrop, dear.
A zombie is a dead person who comes\nback to life and crawls out of the grave.
People come back when they're dead?!
Oh, I'm sorry. Did I frighten you?
There's really nothing to worry about;\nthis is just a fun Halloween costume!\nI'm not ACTUALLY a zombie.
I suppose it's difficult for one of her age\nto make that sort of distinction.
Anna, stop that at once!\nThis isn't your sister.
Forgive me, ma'am, but who exactly\ndoes your daughter think I am?
I'm so sorry. She had an older sister who\npassed away and... Well, I suppose she\nthinks you are her.
A similar height and build, but that's it.\nFrankly, you're not even the same race.
Yes, I was wondering about that.\nEr, so then, why does she...?
She's never really been able to\naccept my Emilia's death.
I think she understands in her head,\nbut in her heart...
At home, she'll suddenly get up and go\nlooking for Emilia until she remembers\nthat she's gone. Then come the tears...
Why do you look so sad, Sis?\nAre you okay? Does your tummy hurt?
Er, n-no! I'm fine! No hurt tummy here!
Yay! Then c'mon, let's go home.
Whoa, hold up! Sweetie, I'm really sorry,\nbut I'm not your sister!
Well, I'm DRESSED as a zombie, but—
I knew it! You ARE Emilia!\nYou came back for me!
(Oh, this is just so sad. How am I going to\nfix things with this poor girl...?)
Listen. Zombies are like ghosts, all right?\nThey're dead bodies that still move around.
But YOU are a living human, which means\nthe two of us can't stay togeth—
I don't care if you're a dead zombie!\nI wanna stay with yooooou!
You really miss her, don't you?
Oh dear. I know this is terribly improper,\nbut might you come live with us and\npretend to be her sister?
Then you want me to lie to her?\nWill that really help anything?
I know how mad it sounds, but I think the\npoor child needs her sister's help to heal.
Please, I beg of you: Just for a little while,\nuntil her heart is whole again.
...All right. If I can be of help,\nI'll do all that I'm able.
I don't have the words to thank you.
Isn't that nice, Anna? Your sister is going\nto be with us again!
YAAAAAAY! Let's play a whole lot,\njust like we did before!
O-of course we will, uh, Anna...
(I'm not certain I make a convincing sister,\nbut I'll do what I can.)
(This is something only a zombie could do\nfor her, so I must make it count!)
